						               													<description>Tarots fulfill their responsibility faithfully until a mysterious purple force born from the chaos. It disrupted the long-standing balance and destroyed the shackles that restrained Tarots.&amp;#10;Tarots were thus contaminated and the world began to be in turmoil...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At this point, the creator of Tarot: &amp;quot;Oracle&amp;quot;, has called you to be his messenger.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will gain the ability to summon other Tarots for a short time so as to find out the &amp;quot;true identity&amp;quot; of the contaminated Tarots. &amp;#10;Now, raise the Tarot Sword to defeat and purify them. Bring the world back to peace again!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a logical reasoning game.&amp;#10;Players will incarnate into a hidden tarot messenger to assist Oracle. Use the ability of Tarots to find out the contaminated Tarots and purify them by guessing their numbers. ( Each Tarot has a corresponding number. )&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;Each player chooses 1 card in the hand and face it down to become a &amp;quot;identity card&amp;quot;. The identity card is hidden information and should not be seen by other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In your turn, you can perform one of the following actions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Activate card effects: Face-up the tarot card to the corresponding position.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Guess Identity: Face-down the tarot card to the hidden area and guess a player's identity card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Change Identity: Discard your original identify card and 1 card in your hand, and then face-down another card as your new identity card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each Tarot Cards has it own effect and you can use them to reason your opponents' identity card number.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When doing Guess Identity, if you correctly guess your opponent's identity card number then the player will be out. When you Guess Identity successfully, you can do one more round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when there is only one player left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
